<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Organ" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Organ,</orth> 1) natural instrument: <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.228" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 228</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 4, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.2.123" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 2, 123</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.623" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 623</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.301" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 301</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 49</bibl>.<lb />2) any instrument: <cit><quote>and given his deputation all the --s of our own power,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 1, 21</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his powerful sound within an o. weak,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.1.179" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 1, 179</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>there is much music in this little o.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.385" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 385</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that I might be the o.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 4.7.71" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 71</bibl></cit>.
